snippet: As much as I love Khan Academy and the lessons in the app, we're not really loving the app itself. I think this app is great for younger kids, but I think it could use some improvements for kids older than five.

title: A Google user
snippet: First of all, I must give my gratitude to the Developers of this app. My child loves it and is learning lots from it. And the Super Simple Songs integrated with the games are really great. But the app tends to have some seriously glitchy behaviours. It often shuts off in mid-game and takes the user to the phone home screen. It freezes at that point for some time with a black screen and when trying to getting back into it, it resets the game so my child loses where the game left off. It's a real test of patience at that age. I have had to restart my phone in order to get it to work again sometimes. On another note, certain things that are required to be either clicked or dragged are placed way to close to the top of the screen, which oftentimes causes my child to activate the slide-in menu from the phone during some games. Also a minor thing, when there's a song involved, there are moments where the song is paused in order to begin an interactive game. But the songs are often paused on odd times. It's really not so crucial but it triggers my OCD to some degree. I would suggest to try to tackle that with a little more finesse :) I realize it's in beta but I hope they pay attention to these things when the time comes to launch the real thing. Other than the things I mentioned, we really love this app!
response: {'title': 'Khan Academy', 'snippet': "Thanks for the comments. We value your input and have communicated your ideas for product improvement to our development team. We're especially glad to hear that your child is learning from the app, and are working hard to continue improving the experience.", 'date': 'October 19, 2018', 'iso_date': '2018-10-19T20:21:37Z'}

title: Caleb Peterson
snippet: Not only is it thoughtfully created and structured, but it is free, AND there are NO adds! I could not ask for more! My daughter loves the learning games, and I love how they vary the teaching. For example, if she is learning the letter sound "a", it will have her work on a but also throw in other letters during the same game so she gets a variety and a well rounded review. I am very grateful for this!
